# Trading Logic Rules

## Signal Engine
- Estimate fair probability from resolution source + time remaining.
- Compare fair probability to CLOB best bid/ask and available depth.
- Account for: spread, taker fee, slippage, latency buffer, adverse-selection buffer, min edge threshold.
- Emit SignalUpdate for every evaluated opportunity — even skipped ones.
- Every skip must include a reason.
- Market phases: opening (small, wider threshold), main (normal), late (reduce inventory), final seconds (avoid unless explicitly enabled).

## Risk Engine — HARD GATES
- Max paper loss per market.
- Max paper notional per market.
- Max paper notional per asset.
- Max total paper notional.
- Max correlated exposure across BTC, ETH, SOL.
- Stale reference feed → halt.
- Stale/disconnected Polymarket WebSocket → halt.
- Geoblock blocked → halt.
- Excessive order rate → halt.
- Clock drift → warn or halt per config.
- Daily paper drawdown halt.
- Risk engine is AUTHORITATIVE. No paper order can bypass risk checks.
- Every halt and rejection must be persisted with a reason.

## Paper Executor
- NEVER submit real orders.
- Maker simulation: assume conservative queue position (behind visible resting size).
- Maker fill: only after observed trade volume exceeds assumed queue ahead.
- Taker simulation: consume visible book depth, include fees and slippage.
- Track positions by market, token, asset.
- Track realized and unrealized P&L.
- Every paper order must have a complete audit trail: why placed, why filled/canceled/missed.

## State
- Decision snapshots must be internally consistent (one coherent view of book + market + reference + position).
- Stale state must be explicit — downstream modules must not silently infer staleness.
- Order book updates must be deterministic: same event sequence → same book state.
